cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.RO, cs.MM, cs.LG 

The paper deals with the problem of estimating the alignment pose between two models using structure-specific local descriptors. This involves generating descriptors using a combination of 2D image data and 3D contextual shape data, resulting in a set of semi-local descriptors containing rich appearance and shape information for both edge and texture structures. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the estimation of alignment pose, which is a common problem in Robotics (cs.RO) and Graphics (cs.GR). The use of descriptors and feature space relations also suggests that the paper may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
